text.text:
Great Locals' Hangout - Wonderful Food & Service - Reservations strongly advised

We took a tram to get to this restaurant. It is conveniently located 1 minute walk from the Hürth Fischenich tram station. The restaurant opens at 5 pm, and when we arrived half an hour early, we were asked to wait. We took a walk around the block and spent some time at the Rosellenplatz, a lovely little park about 3 minutes’ walk away. We came back exactly at 5 and were seated, though, did not have a reservation. You must know that by 6 pm the place was completely packed. There were no free tables on the terrace, and it was a Tuesday. Locals with their friends and families really favor this place.

We started with a chanterelle soup and a carpaccio de manzo. The soup was thick with mushroomsand very tasty; generous portions in a large bowl. The carpaccio was pretty standard, a bit overchilled, which made its texture a little watery.

For the main course we ordered three chanterelle dishes. The chef used exactly the same sauce with mushrooms for each dish, so the chanterelles were prepared exactly the same. The sauce was very good, creamy and light, the mushroom portions and sizes generous. It was no problem that it was exactly the same, the taste was what mattered.

The Summer Plate had chicken breast covered with the mushroom sauce, accompanied by fried potatoes and zucchini and a small salad. Chicken was nicely cooked, tender and juicy. The potatoes tasted exactly like home made and the salad was very fresh with light dressing. Two other main courses were the Veal and the Rump Steak. We asked for the steak to be cooked medium rare, it was perfectly prepared. The veal was good too, but the rump steak had more flavor. The potato croquettes that accompanied both meats were delicious, not at all oily.

Service was wonderful, once we were seated the food was brought in promptly. Our waiter was very courteous and professional. A definite must visit. Would love to go back again.

I would ideally like to give 2 stars, once for eating on site and once for ordering. That's why there are only 4 stars.
Everything on site is top notch, the food is fresh and super tasty. The daily menu is always imaginative. I can highly praise the friendliness, even when the shop is full at lunchtime.
I would like to give it 5 stars.
For me it's the best Italian in Hürth.

Unfortunately it's a little different when ordering,
The first time everything was great.
You can order via Lieferando, WhatsApp or telephone.
We have already tested all 3 variants.
I can't say which one is best. In terms of speed, they are all the same speed and, in my opinion, pretty fast, which is good if you are extremely hungry.
As far as the quality goes, I'm unfortunately a little disappointed.
At least the food is warm, but my child ordered pasta with cream sauce and spinach and she gets a gorgonzola sauce, which she absolutely doesn't like.
I ordered pasta with salmon and tomatoes in a cream sauce and that was anything but what I had ordered, salmon and pasta were there, but it was a simple tomato sauce with maybe a little cream, there were no tomatoes and no dill I was exactly looking forward to it.
My better half had pizza rolls and a pizza frutti di mare because there was no more scampi.
Unfortunately, the pizza rolls were rock hard and so was the herb butter.
What I don't know about Made in Italy either.
The employee seemed pretty annoyed on the phone, and it wasn't Pierro either, because he's always friendly on the phone.
Absolutely recommended locally, but can only be ordered from Pierro personally. Unfortunately, everything else was just a careless affair for me.

Where to start... :D

The location... well! The Mady in Italy is located in the industrial area of ​​Hürth... But it has a beautiful outdoor terrace (mostly covered!) and a lovingly furnished shop.

Service: I don't think it could be friendlier! Always a smile on your face, always courteous, the atmosphere you get from the open kitchen is always relaxed and the customers are also very friendly, there's a kind of "you eat together so you know each other" - mentality that you otherwise only know from your vacation in Italy! The main language is clearly Italian, but a perfect Italian-tinged Rhenish language is also spoken! :D

The food - BOMBASTIC! I've been eating there every other day for over six months and I'm surprised every time! Always recommended: “Lunch!” - For 10-12€ you get a generous salad/bruschetta and a decent lunch (different every day!), from steak to thick schnitzel to pasta, the palate is really pampered here! :D

The food always tastes "like mom/grandma's", even though there are only men in the kitchen...but they say they have copied their skills from their mother :D

EVERY special request is fulfilled straight away, the drink is on the house for regular guests with a friendly wave and you really feel right at home here! :D

originalText.text:
Wo soll man anfangen... :D

Die Lage... naja! Das Mady in Italy liegt eben im Industriegebiet von Hürth... Hat aber eine schöne Außenterrasse (größtenteils überdacht!) und ein liebevoll eingerichtetes Ladenlokal.

Service: Ich glaube freundlicher geht es nicht! Immer ein Lachen im Gesicht, immer zuvorkommend, die Stimmung die man aus der offenen Küche mitbekommt ist immer locker und auch die Kunden sind sehr freundlich, es herrscht so eine Art "man-isst-zusammen-also-kennt-man-sich"-mentalität, wie man sie sonst nur aus dem Italien-Urlaub kennt! Hauptsprache ist eindeutig italienisch, es wird aber auch ein 1A italienisch angehauchtes rheinländisch gesprochen! :D

Das Essen - BOMBASTISCH! Ich komme seit über einem halben Jahr jeden zweiten Tag dort essen und bin jedes mal wieder überrascht! Immer wieder zu empfehlen: "Mittagstisch!" - Für 10-12€ bekommt man einen großzügigen Salat/Bruschetta und ein ordentliches Mittagessen (jeden Tag anders!), von Steak über dicke Schnitzel bis hin zu Pasta wird hier echt der Gaumen verwöhnt! :D

Das Essen schmeckt immer "wie bei Mama/Oma", und das obwohl hier nur Männer in der Küche stehen...die aber, nach eigener Aussage, ihre Skills von ihrer Mutter abgeschaut haben :D

JEDER Sonderwunsch wird direkt erfüllt, das Getränk geht für Stammgäste mit einem netten Abwinken auch mal aufs Haus und man fühlt sich hier echt pudelwohl! :D

text.text:
Great Locals' Hangout - Wonderful Food & Service - Reservations strongly advised

We took a tram to get to this restaurant. It is conveniently located 1 minute walk from the Hürth Fischenich tram station. The restaurant opens at 5 pm, and when we arrived half an hour early, we were asked to wait. We took a walk around the block and spent some time at the Rosellenplatz, a lovely little park about 3 minutes’ walk away. We came back exactly at 5 and were seated, though, did not have a reservation. You must know that by 6 pm the place was completely packed. There were no free tables on the terrace, and it was a Tuesday. Locals with their friends and families really favor this place.

We started with a chanterelle soup and a carpaccio de manzo. The soup was thick with mushroomsand very tasty; generous portions in a large bowl. The carpaccio was pretty standard, a bit overchilled, which made its texture a little watery.

For the main course we ordered three chanterelle dishes. The chef used exactly the same sauce with mushrooms for each dish, so the chanterelles were prepared exactly the same. The sauce was very good, creamy and light, the mushroom portions and sizes generous. It was no problem that it was exactly the same, the taste was what mattered.

The Summer Plate had chicken breast covered with the mushroom sauce, accompanied by fried potatoes and zucchini and a small salad. Chicken was nicely cooked, tender and juicy. The potatoes tasted exactly like home made and the salad was very fresh with light dressing. Two other main courses were the Veal and the Rump Steak. We asked for the steak to be cooked medium rare, it was perfectly prepared. The veal was good too, but the rump steak had more flavor. The potato croquettes that accompanied both meats were delicious, not at all oily.

Service was wonderful, once we were seated the food was brought in promptly. Our waiter was very courteous and professional. A definite must visit. Would love to go back again.

2. Good vegetarian pita: The vegetarian pita was a highlight. The filling was tasteful and well balanced, proving that vegetarian dishes are great here too.
